I think signed/unsigned mixed calculation is wrong.

Sample code is below.

 module mod(A);
  output [7:0]         A;
  wire [7:0]           B;
  wire signed [3:0]    C;
  assign    C=-1;
  assign    B=3;
  assign    A=B+C;
 endmodule

Verilator outputs A=-2(Wrong)
But
NC-Verilog outputs A=18(Correct)


In this case, 
all number have to use unsigned.
